# Test fixtures import package:flutter (a dev-only dependency of this pure-Dart
# lint package) and are test data only — not needed by consumers. Excluding
# them keeps the published archive clean (no missing-dependency warnings).
test/

# Do NOT ship the example's analysis_options.yaml. It activates the custom_lint
# analyzer plugin (`analyzer: plugins: [custom_lint]`). pana's downgrade
# analysis (`dart pub downgrade` + `dart analyze .`) descends into example/,
# honours that file, and bootstraps the custom_lint plugin — whose own
# `dart pub get`/build then FAILS at the downgraded floors (e.g. matcher 0.12.10
# references CastError/NullThrownError, removed in Dart 3), surfacing as
# pana's `[pub-downgrade-error]` and tanking the score. Mature custom_lint
# packages (riverpod_lint) avoid this by never shipping a plugin-activating
# example. The repo keeps this file for in-IDE dogfooding; consumers enable the
# plugin per the example README's "Enable the plugin" section.
example/analysis_options.yaml
